10:
This can't be happening... He has to
be alive out there!
23:
You took a nasty tumble off a cliff. I
found you half-dead. Eat this.
29:
I'm Alk. Can I get a name for my
savior?
35:
Well, Sir Vargen, thanks for patching
me up and feeding me.
37:
Just call me Vargen. You need more
rest. Lay back down and take it easy.
44:
Stop squirming. These herbs will
treat your wounds and help with the
swelling.
48:
Huh... Never seen these kinds of
herbs before.
51:
The townspeople probably don't
know they exist. I've never told them.
53: Been ten years since I last visited.
56:
You've been living alone out here...
for a whole decade?
59:
I used to be an adventurer. But living
in these woods suits me better.
61:
I'm heading out to hunt. You could
use the protein.
67:
Looks like my limbs are working just
fine! It's about time—
74:
Yeah. My friends are probably
worried sick.
76: I'll show you out of the woods then.
86:
You can come out now. I don't sense
any more monsters around.
90:
Appreciate the protection, but... I'm
healed up enough to take on a few
monsters, you know?
93: I know. I just wanted the exercise.
95:
Anyway, the town's over yonder. This
is where we part ways.
101:
S-sorry, I'm not making fun of you, I
swear. It's just... you remind me of
someone.
106:
Yeah, you and her are like peas in a
pod.
118:
Looks like your welcoming party's
here.
123:
U-um, hey! If you ever feel like going
for a change of pace and come
visit...
126:
You should join us for a few
adventures!
138: Alk! I'm so glad you're safe.
143:
Where have you been?! I've been
worried sick, young man!
147:
S-sorry! A guy who lives in the
woods saved me and nursed me
back to health.
149:
He was super nice, but... I don't know
if I'll ever see him again—
153: You mean that person over there?
157:
Feeling like a change of pace
already?
161: Yeah. I've been due for one, I think.
